<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>When QPickingSettings::pickMode() is set to QPickingSettings::TrianglePicking, the signals on QObjectPicker will carry an instance of QPickTriangleEvent.</db:para>
<db:para>This contains the details of the triangle that was picked.</db:para>
<db:note>
<db:para>In case of indexed rendering, the point indices are relative to the array of indices, not the array of coordinates.</db:para>
</db:note>
